-- Brazil's Banco Cruzeiro do Sul Sells $200 Million of International Bonds
-- Gabrielle Coppola
-- 2010-06-30T22:44:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/brazil-s-banco-cruzeiro-do-sul-sells-200-million-of-international-bonds.html

          
          
             Banco Cruzeiro do Sul SA, the
Brazilian bank that specializes in payroll-deductible loans,
sold $200 million of three-year notes to yield 7.25 percent,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  
 BCP Securities arranged the offering.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Gabrielle Coppola in New York at 
 gcoppola@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        